16/10/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The summit of Central and Southeast European leaders in Zagreb ended Saturday (15 October) with a joint call by participants for continuation of the EU enlargement process.
The two-day event drew 16 presidents of countries in the region.
Speaking to reporters, Croatian President Stipe Mesic said the message was especially important in light of dilemmas emerging within the EU in recent months.
Next year, the summit will take place in Bulgaria.
(Novi list - 16/10/05;
Hina, PBS BiH - 15/10/05)
